Xqmail is a secure, reliable, efficient, simple message transfer agent.
XIt is meant as a replacement for the entire sendmail-binmail system on
Xtypical Internet-connected UNIX hosts.
X
Xqmail supports host and user masquerading, full host hiding, virtual 
Xdomains, null clients, list-owner rewriting, relay control, double-bounce 
Xrecording, arbitrary RFC 822 address lists, cross-host mailing list loop 
Xdetection, per-recipient checkpointing, downed host backoffs, independent 
Xmessage retry schedules, etc. qmail also includes a drop-in ``sendmail'' 
Xwrapper so that it will be used transparently by your current UAs.
X
Xa pop3 server is included in the package, and various add-on utilities
X(including mailing list processors, a tool for dial-up connections to
Xseparate local and remote mail, log analysers, etc) are available.
X
XMore information is available at http://www.qmail.org/.
X
X					stuart@helan.org
X					28 June, 1998
END-of-qmail/pkg/DESCR
